        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 2:18PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 217 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Stanford, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stanford, Windham, Moccasin, and Benchland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
